answers.a: E140 is a food color additive (chlorophylls and chlorophyllins), not a Corolla model code; it’s a plant-derived green color approved for use in foods in the EU and many countries.

answers.q: how do you start a john deere e140
answers.a: That refers to a lawn tractor; E140 in foods denotes chlorophyll-based green colorants used to impart a green hue to products.
Mower pricing isn’t applicable; E140 is a food coloring used at low levels under good manufacturing practice (quantum satis).

answers.q: how much oil does a john deere e140 hold?
answers.a: Unrelated to the additive; E140 includes oil‑soluble chlorophylls and water‑soluble chlorophyllins, used in small amounts to color foods.

answers.q: how much oil does a john deere e140 take
answers.a: Also unrelated; E140 is an additive incorporated into oil- or water-based formulations depending on whether chlorophylls or chlorophyllins are used.
